## v1.4.0 (2026-05-17)

**Changed by:** ProjectAgamemnon downstream-PR-queue triage session -- 2026-05-17
**Verification:** verified-ci -- fix-main PR #393 merged; 14 downstream PRs unblocked after rebase

### What changed
- Added new failed-attempt row: "Single-repo broken main not detected before rebasing downstream PRs" -- pre-flight `gh run list --branch main` check required before any rebase
- Added new subsection under Results & Parameters: "Single-Repo Application (Agamemnon 2026-05-17)" with pre-flight check command and 6-step recovery sequence
- Added ProjectAgamemnon 2026-05-17 session to Verified On table

### Why
ProjectAgamemnon had 6 open PRs (#387-#392) all showing `mergeStateStatus: BLOCKED`. The initial
hypothesis was "PRs need rebase to retrigger CI", but after rebasing all 6 onto a fresh
`origin/main` the CI re-ran and they failed identically. Root cause: `main` itself had been
broken since PR #286 merged (find_package(OpenSSL) + clang-tidy `modernize-use-nodiscard` /
`misc-include-cleaner` on `circuit_breaker.cpp/.hpp` + missing `MockGitHubClient::fail_list_on_label`
field). Every downstream PR's matrix inherited the failure. The recovery required a dedicated
`fix-ci-*` PR merged FIRST, then rebasing downstream PRs (also re-arming auto-merge after each
force-push). The pre-flight `gh run list --branch main` check would have detected the broken
main immediately and avoided the wasted rebase cycle.

